### Phase 7 — Habit Modal Enhancements
File: `stokely-frontend/src/components/Dashboard/NewHabitModal.tsx` + `NewHabitModal.css`

**7A. Icon Picker**
- New file: `stokely-frontend/src/utils/habitIcons.ts` — curated list of ~60 lucide icon names
- `IconPicker` component (inline in modal): search input + scrollable grid of icon buttons
- Dynamic render: `const Icon = (LucideIcons as Record<string, any>)[name]`
- `icon-grid`: `display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(2.5rem, 1fr)); gap: 0.4rem; max-height: 200px; overflow-y: auto`
- Selected icon shown next to habit name in `Habit.tsx`: `const Icon = LucideIcons[habitData.icon]` rendered at 18px beside the name

**7B. Recurrence End Date**
- Two preset buttons ("Indefinitely" / "Until date") matching existing `.preset-btn` style
- When "Until date" selected: `<input type="date" className="modal-input">` with `color-scheme: dark` and `min={today}`
- State: `const [recurrenceEnd, setRecurrenceEnd] = useState<string | null>(null)`
- Populate from `habitToEdit.recurrenceEnd` in edit mode

**7C. Notes**
- `<textarea className="modal-input modal-textarea">` below name field
- CSS: `resize: vertical; min-height: 80px; font-family: inherit`

**7D. Reminders**
- `<input type="time">` with clear button
- On submit with reminder set: `registerServiceWorker()` → `getVapidKey()` → `subscribeToPush()` → `api.push.subscribe()`
- Convert local time ↔ UTC before send/display
- Handle notification permission denial gracefully with toast

**7E. E2E Placeholder** (bottom of modal, fully disabled)
```tsx
<div style={{ opacity: 0.35, pointerEvents: 'none' }}>
    <h4>End-to-End Encryption — Coming Soon</h4>
    <p>Notes and habit names will be encrypted client-side.</p>
    <button disabled>Enable Encryption</button>
</div>
```

